author: Sarah D.
title: The verdict is in! Neil Gorsuch just had Dick Durbin for breakfast (and didn’t break a sweat)
text:
— Matt Welch (@MattWelch) March 21, 2017 
OK, Dick Durbin … you’re up! This is your chance to torpedo Judge Gorsuch’s confirmation, so make it count. 
Let’s check in on Tricky Dick’s performance: #Gorsuch asked about letter by student accusing him of encouraging discrimination against pregnant female lawyers https://t.co/yKRbDMW3i2 pic.twitter.com/kf0kdO1mFD 
— Fox News (@FoxNews) March 21, 2017 Holy crap. This is just a wipe out. Look at Durbin being a jackass, and the way Gorsuch handles it with this answer. https://t.co/sZJAoGWpbw 
— Mike Dury (@MikeDury) March 21, 2017 
Man. Durbin is really not good at this. Actually, he doesn’t seem to be good at anything today. That’s bad news for him … but great news for viewers. I think Durbin's trying to break Gorsuch but it's not happening. #GorsuchHearing 
— Jess Clackum (@JessicaClackum) March 21, 2017 Wow, did #gorsuch just demolish durbin in that exchange about the law school incident… 
— Jeffrey Toobin (@JeffreyToobin) March 21, 2017 In response to Durbin, #Gorsuch just gave one of the most erudite and detailed defense of Hobby Lobby ever offered. #GorsuchHearing 
— Nate Madden (@NateMaddenCR) March 21, 2017 Shorter Durbin: judges should fix laws if Congress screws the up. Judge Gorsuch: don't screw it up in the first place. #GorsuchHearing 
— Dan Isett (@DanIsett) March 21, 2017 Gorsuch, responding to Durbin's Univ. of Colorado question: pic.twitter.com/IDBhcCh04b 
— Dave Mitchell (@the4thdave) March 21, 2017 Gorsuch to Durbin. pic.twitter.com/DEe9hRkzLO 
— Heather Champion (@winningatmylife) March 21, 2017 Gorsuch v. Durbin 
— Hobart Scales (@Hobiescales) March 21, 2017 "My job is not to write the law Senator it is to apply the law" Gorsuch to Durbin #GorsuchHearing pic.twitter.com/3h9kDdF24T
